HEADWORD: Nephelite
<hw>Neph"e*lite</hw> <pr>(n⟦ecr⟧f"⟦esl⟧*l⟦imac⟧t)</pr> }</mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>nefe`lh</grk> cloud: cf. F.
<ets>n⟦eacute⟧ph⟦eacute⟧line</ets>. Cf. <er>Nebula</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral occurring at Vesuvius, in glassy
hexagonal crystals; also elsewhere, in grayish or greenish masses having
a greasy luster, as the variety elaeolite. It is a silicate of aluminia,
soda, and potash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

